3. cs.NA (Numerical Analysis): The simplex algorithm is a numerical method for solving linear programming problems, which falls under the category of numerical analysis. The paper provides lower bounds for pivot rules used in the simplex algorithm, which is relevant to numerical analysis. 
4. cs.GT (Computer Science and Game Theory): The paper deals with pivot rules used in the simplex algorithm, which is a topic of interest in game theory. The lower bounds on AUSO of the abstract cube are also related to game theory.
